This paper discusses the use of prediction markets for machine learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of utility-based frameworks, which is related to game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of market mechanisms for probabilistic modeling, which is related to multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
